<h1>Problem 942 - 2012 IMOSL, C2</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(n \geq 1\) be an integer. What is the maximum number of disjoint pairs of elements of the set \(\{ 1,2,\ldots , n \}\) such that the sums of the different pairs are different integers not exceeding \(n\)?</p>
<h2>Thinking</h2>
<div class=skib>
